                <h1>Time for another update to instant replay</h1>
                
                                    <figure class="dom-art-container my-4">
                                                    <img src="https://snworksceo.imgix.net/dtc/7864bb8c-d78b-4fd1-bc8c-3af5850cb2c7.sized-1000x1000.jpg?w=1000" alt="&lt;p&gt;Defensive&#x20;penalties&#x20;on&#x20;Breon&#x20;Borders&#x20;and&#x20;company&#x20;currently&#x20;cannot&#x20;be&#x20;reviewed&#x20;under&#x20;the&#x20;NCAA&#x27;s&#x20;replay&#x20;system,&#x20;which&#x20;is&#x20;the&#x20;same&#x20;one&#x20;used&#x20;in&#x20;the&#x20;NFL.&amp;nbsp&#x3B;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;" class="w-100">
                                                <div class="domphoto-caption mt-2 text-left text-md-right">
                            <p>Defensive penalties on Breon Borders and company currently cannot be reviewed under the NCAA's replay system, which is the same one used in the NFL.&nbsp;</p>

                                                             <aside class="photo-caption photo-credit d-block pl-1">
                                    <figcaption class="d-block">
                                                                                    Photo by <a href="https://www.dukechronicle.com/staff/sanjeev-dasgupta">Sanjeev Dasgupta</a> |
                                                                                                                                The Chronicle
                                                                            </figcaption>
                                </aside>
                            
                        </div>
                    </figure>
                
                                    <div class="row  mt-4 mb-0 mb-md-4">
                        <div class="col-12 col-md-6">
                            <aside class="author-name">
                                    
    
                                    
            By <a href="https://www.dukechronicle.com/staff/ben-feder">Ben Feder</a>
                                    
                                <div class="mt-1">
                                    <span class="can-localize">October 18, 2016 | 12:14am EDT</span>
                                </div>
                            </aside>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-12 col-md-6 text-left text-md-right d-print-none">
                            <ul class="social-links list-unsyled list-inline mt-4 mt-md-0">
                                <li class="list-inline-item"><a href="http://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?u=https://www.dukechronicle.com/article/2016/10/time-for-another-update-to-instant-replay" target="_blank" class="sends-events" data-ga-category="Share" data-ga-action="click" data-ga-label="facebook" data-ga-value="CURL"><i class="fab fa-facebook"></i></a></li>
                                <li class="list-inline-item"><a href="http://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=https://www.dukechronicle.com/article/2016/10/time-for-another-update-to-instant-replay&amp;text=Time for another update to instant replay" target="_blank" class="sends-events" data-ga-category="Share" data-ga-action="click" data-ga-label="twitter" data-ga-value="CURL"><i class="fab fa-twitter"></i></a></li>
                                                                <li class="list-inline-item"><a href="mailto:?subject=Time%20for%20another%20update%20to%20instant%20replay%20|%20The%20Chronicle&amp;message=Check%20out%20this%20article%20from%20The%20Chronicle%3A%20https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dukechronicle.com%2Farticle%2F2016%2F10%2Ftime-for-another-update-to-instant-replay" class="sends-events" data-ga-category="Share" data-ga-action="click" data-ga-label="email" data-ga-value="CURL"><i class="fa fa-envelope"></i></a></li>
                                <li class="list-inline-item"><a href="#" onclick="window.print()" class="sends-events" data-ga-category="Share" data-ga-action="click" data-ga-label="facebook" data-ga-value="CURL"><i class="fas fa-print"></i></a></li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                
                <div class="article-content w-100 mb-4">
                                            <p>Once again, another team has been&nbsp;victimized by the NFL’s system for calling penalties&mdash;more specifically, by its rule that does not allow instant replay to apply to pass interference.&nbsp;</p>
<p>This time it was the Atlanta Falcons, who lost after&nbsp;an obvious defensive pass
interference call was missed on 4th-and-10.</p>

                        <div class="inline-ad float-none float-md-left my-4 mr-0 mr-md-4 text-center d-print-none">
                            <!-- START gryphon/ads/rectangle-inline.tpl -->
            <div id="azk18664"></div>
    <!-- END gryphon/ads/rectangle-inline.tpl -->
                        </div>

                        <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/qxrNZYJnJsE" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
<p class="MsoNormal">But Sunday's example with Seattle All-Pro cornerback Richard Sherman preventing Falcons wideout Julio Jones from going up for a catch is just the latest showing why instant replay should apply to pass interference.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">The problem has reared its ugly head time and time again.&nbsp;In 2013, a hotly contested decision to not&nbsp;<a href="http://bleacherreport.com/articles/1514765-did-jimmy-smith-hold-michael-crabtree-on-4th-and-ballgame">call defensive pass interference</a> against the Baltimore Ravens&nbsp;changed the outcome of the Super Bowl,&nbsp;but more than three years later, neither the&nbsp;NFL nor NCAA&nbsp;has made any progress in finding a solution to the problem.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">To clarify, not every pass interference call or no-call is incorrect. There just needs to be someone else making sure that the on-field decision is correct before continuing the game.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"></p>
<!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>
